 King William's Town - Following advice that one of its Solid Waste Management employees tested positive for COVID-19, the Buffalo City Municipality said it decided to close the King William's Town Botanical Gardens Depot with immediate effect. "As a precautionary measure, King William's Town Botanical Gardens Depot is temporarily closed until Thursday for deep cleansing and decontamination," the Metro said. "Please note that refuse removal services will be disrupted in the following areas (Wednesday and Thursday)." "The Municipality is aware that it’s essential services staff are in the frontline of offering services and every measures are being taken to ensure their safety," it added. "We have issued all our staff with PPEs and have been regularly screened and assisting the Department of Health with testing our employees." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 